cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about improving Neural Machine Translation (NMT) by incorporating target side syntactic structure through latent variables. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also introduces a new latent variable model and a neural expectation maximization algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. Additionally, the paper mentions that the model is based on a transformer-based NMT system, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the model on four different MT tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as machine translation is a task related to computer vision.
